Apache Arrow is a columnar in-memory format that provides several benefits for high-performance data processing. To use it with Ballista, you need to enable the Arrow plugin and configure the query execution plan.

    First, add the following dependency to your `Cargo.toml` file:
    ```toml
    [dependencies]
    arrow = "5"
    ```

    Next, create a custom query execution plan that uses Apache Arrow as the in-memory format. You can do this by creating a new struct that implements the `QueryExecutionPlan` trait and overrides the `build_plan` method.

    Here's an example:
    ```rust
    use ballista::execution_plan::{QueryExecutionPlan, QueryPlanBuilder};
    use arrow::datatypes::{DataType, Field};

    #[derive(Debug)]
    pub struct ArrowPlan {
        // Define the data types for each column.
        columns: Vec<(String, DataType)>,
    }

    impl QueryExecutionPlan for ArrowPlan {
        fn build_plan(&self) -> QueryPlanBuilder<Self> {
            let mut builder = QueryPlanBuilder::new(self.columns.len());

            // Add each column to the plan builder.
            for (name, data_type) in &self.columns {
                builder.add_column(name.to_string(), DataChunkFormat::Arrow, data_type);
            }

            builder
        }
    }

    // Create an instance of ArrowPlan and use it as the query execution plan.
    let arrow_plan = ArrowPlan {
        columns: vec![
            ("id".to_string(), DataType::Int32),
            ("name".to_string(), DataType::Utf8),
            ("age".to_string(), DataType::Int32),
        ],
    };

    // Create a Ballista connection and use the custom query execution plan.
    let conn = ballista::Connection::new("sqlite:// memory:").unwrap();
    conn.execute_query(&arrow_plan, "SELECT * FROM users").unwrap();
    ```

    This example demonstrates how to create a custom query execution plan that uses Apache Arrow as the in-memory format. By enabling the Arrow plugin and configuring the query execution plan, you can take advantage of Arrow's performance benefits.

